        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-217521" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-217521" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Believing issues, rightly or wrongly, are interconnected makes people an extremist? This is laughable Mattew. You&#8217;ve started off with a conclusion &#8211; UKIP are extremists &#8211; and are then scrabbling around trying to find a justification, and come up with an embarrassingly poor one. If people like you tried to be logical (e.g. start with reasoning the pros and cons, and then create a conclusion based on those pros and cons later) then you would be much more rigorous in your thinking. You might even change your mind on some other issues. e.g. the idea that some small amount of influence in the rule-making process for the European market is worth more than the economic returns from FTAs from a dozen other markets.</p>
