            <div id="dsq-comment-message-217881" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Matthew, what is happening? I always enjoyed your pieces and thought you a sensible chap but this dismissal of the disgruntlement of millions of Britons suggests a sad lack of empathy. Can you really put your hand on your heart and say that that there is no metropolitan elite, no bien pensant core of British society? Thinks of my question next time you are quaffing champagne and canapes. Given all that has gone wrong in Britain in recent years, and the failure of the political class to respond to it in any way except to say that they know better and their critics are illiterate extremist louts, it is not surprising that many are looking to a new party &#8212; Alex Salmon and the SNP in Scot and UKIP in England. As a Conservative who really cannot stomach Cameron, Osborne, and Hague&#8211;and who wants a partial disengagement from the EU&#8211;my only home is UKIP at the moment. My vote is a protest vote and I have few expectations but I am not going to vote for politicians who simply put me down by telling me they know better.</p>
