            <div id="dsq-comment-message-217981" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>This really is nonsense Mr Parris.</p>
<p>I well remember delivering election leaflets in 1979 in which the Labour Party parodied your position on housing. You may recall it: you had taken a reasonable position as to someone&#8217;s entitlement. The Labour Party, feeling afraid of Mrs Thatcher&#8217;s advance, called you extremist. In today&#8217;s terms, I suppose, swivel-eyed.</p>
<p>You were, of course
