<p>When I listen to UKIP&#8217;s potential voters, a common observation is that the only party lead by a leader, rather than by a manager, is UKIP. Farage is lucky to have such colourless opponents.</p>
<p>Cameron&#8217;s referendum offer, after a putative &#8216;re-negotiation is entirely implausible. It is helping UKIP, not hurting them. He would have been better advised to have been honest.</p>
<p>And for sure we would not join the EU now, if we were not already members, would we?</p>
