        <div id="dsq-comment-body-219061" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-219061" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Yeah right. Is Parris not a Liberal extremist? He can&#8217;t bear the idea of UKIP – a party which stands diametrically opposite him. Well watch them take a huge bite out of CONLAB&#8217;s voting rumps. Lib Dems, bye bye for the next 30 years&#8230;.not nice knowing you. Maybe you&#8217;ll pop up next in Labour&#8217;s bed&#8230;they may need you &#8220;prop them up&#8221;. I am sure UKIP like every political party will have its downs, but on a few crisp points they score bullseyes (for me, anyway). Is UKIP peopled by extremists? Yes, perhaps. Ones that might reverse the Labour party&#8217;s own form of extremism that was, under the self-serving Blair. Why did Cameron table a EU referendum in 2017? Because he knows that the yellow and purples are going to marshall the &#8220;sick and tired&#8221; of GB. Rant over.</p>
