            <div id="dsq-comment-message-219701" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Mr Parris</p>
<p>As a longtime Times&#8217; reader, I have enjoyed reading your articles for many years. Similarly, I am a lifelong Tory voter but have become very disgruntled of late.</p>
<p>Where I live there is no doubt that there has been a definite impact on the local demographics secondary to the recent rates of immigration. I had genuine hope Mr Cameron and Mr Osborne would bring a sensible, firm Conservative approach to this and many other problems: sadly, I have been gravely disappointed.</p>
<p>May I ask, as you are much closer to the upper echelons of the Conservative Party, what would be an acceptable level of new immigrants into the UK per annum? Can I ask you don&#8217;t use &#8220;net immigration&#8221; as I think this term is insulting.</p>
<p>I would appreciate your response.</p>
