    <ul class="children">
    <li class="comment even depth-3" id="dsq-comment-221461">
        <div id="dsq-comment-header-221461" class="dsq-comment-header">
            <cite id="dsq-cite-221461">
                <span id="dsq-author-user-221461">pjl20</span>
            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-221461" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-221461" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Martin. Why do I need a lesson in reading?</p>
<p>I do not recognise any of the accusations made against UKIP, in this piece by Matthew Parris.</p>
<p>Surely I would, if these remarks were true, as I mix regularly with party members. </p>
<p>Comments posted on-line on newspaper websites do not guarantee any authenticity, do they?</p>
<p>The many new members who are constantly signing up and joining us are moderates (Procedures exist for checking this out). Even Labour councillors, such as one in Grimsby last week, are now coming over to UKIP.</p>
</div>
        </div>

    <ul class="children">
    <li class="comment odd alt depth-4" id="dsq-comment-221621">
        <div id="dsq-comment-header-221621" class="dsq-comment-header">
            <cite id="dsq-cite-221621">
                <span id="dsq-author-user-221621">martin_lowe</span>
            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-221621" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-221621" class="dsq-comment-message"><p><i>Martin. Why do I need a lesson in reading?</i></p>
<p>Because you asked why Mr Parris believes UKIP are a party of extremists when the article is called &#8220;Why UKIP is a party of extremists&#8221; (which does exactly that).</p>
<p>I know UKIPpers like to ignore facts right in front of their noses and either play dumb or be dumb, but you simply have no excuse for your idiocy in this instance.</p>
</div>
        </div>

    <ul class="children">
    <li class="comment even depth-5" id="dsq-comment-221771">
        <div id="dsq-comment-header-221771" class="dsq-comment-header">
            <cite id="dsq-cite-221771">
                <span id="dsq-author-user-221771">pjl20</span>
            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-221771" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-221771" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>I am an active member of the party, not just a supporter. We have a full manifesto of policies, being a main political party.</p>
<p>I have read some of your comments and I do not agree with them or recognise the criticism made by Matthew Parris.</p>
<p>Extremists have no place in UKIP. This is not a party for them at all. They belong elsewhere, in the EDL, BNP or National Front, for example.</p>
<p>You may not like it or agree with it, but we are a moderate and considerate party with supporters from almost all ethnic groups. How do I know? Because I have met them at party conferences, as party candidates, as members and as donators of funds.</p>
<p>I know that the Tories are getting upset about losing their elected councillors, members and supporters to UKIP. But so are Labour, Lib Dems and even the Green party. (our candidate in the Bradford West By-election, was an ex-Green member)</p>
</div>
        </div>

    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
    <li class="comment odd alt depth-5" id="dsq-comment-221931">
        <div id="dsq-comment-header-221931" class="dsq-comment-header">
            <cite id="dsq-cite-221931">
                <span id="dsq-author-user-221931">martin_lowe</span>
            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-221931" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-221931" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Tell us all about Peter Lucas, the ex-BNP UKIP town councillor in Devon.</p>
<p>Tell us all about Chris Byrne, the ex-BNP member who stood for UKIP in Surrey.</p>
<p>Tell us all about Alan Ryall, the ex-BNP member who stood for UKIP in Suffolk.</p>
<p>Tell us all about Chris Scotton, the UKIP candidate in Leicester who supported many racist and extremist groups on Facebook who only got suspended from UKIP <b>AFTER</b> he featured in the Daily Mail.</p>
<p>UKIP isn&#8217;t a party of extremists? Then why do extremists flock to the BNP in blazers?</p>
</div>
        </div>

    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
    <li class="comment even depth-5" id="dsq-comment-222031">
        <div id="dsq-comment-header-222031" class="dsq-comment-header">
            <cite id="dsq-cite-222031">
                <span id="dsq-author-user-222031">pjl20</span>
            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-222031" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-222031" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>What you mean to say, if these allegations are true, is that we have had some interlopers.</p>
<p>Do really think anyone would openly admit to such deception?</p>
<p>Each of the main parties have had people who have tried to deceive. What does this prove? Such individuals will hardly receive a welcome will they.</p>
<p>Just think we achieved 23+% of the vote in the recent elections held on May 2 and as many as 46.5% in Rotherham where we returned a UKIP councillor in a Labour stronghold. A marvellous result.</p>
<p>All I can say Martin, is that you seem to be most upset by our recent successes. Just imagine what 2014 and 2015 may bring in the European and general elections..</p>
</div>
