            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-221311" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-221311" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>You must be aware that your comments on religion are factually false, and that many of the more mature religions encourage a much more complex, layered and multi-faceted approach to the world than is usual.  Of course, heavily simplified revivalist religion does fit your caricature, but that does not account for the majority of us.</p>
<p>Second, whilst there is such a strong willingness on the Centre and Left to stand up for Saudi-funded fascism, I find it difficult to get that worked up about the domestic right-wing.  Saudi-affiliated groups murder lots of people daily, whereas even the nastiest domestic groups have murdered a few people ever.  If your innuendo is to link mainstream political parties with fascism, then perhaps Andrew Gilligan&#8217;s work in East London is mining a richer seam.</p>
<p>Third, your comments about conspiratorial thinking are quite obviously correct.  Again, the anti-Western, anti-British and anti-English propaganda from the Left is probably your best place to start.  When you have exhausted that, there may well be something for you to investigate at UKIP.</p>
</div>
