            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-221681" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-221681" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>I have read Matthew Parris&#8217;s columns over the years with enjoyment, but I cannot take his views too seriously.  He has written about the weirdness of MP&#8217;s as a class,  the totally outlandish views of the majority of the electorate and the colossal ignorance of most juries.</p>
<p>Then, for good measure, he has come out with &#8220;No columnist should read too much into online responses to what he has written. No more than those who call in to radio phone-in programmes are those who post their comments online representative of readers as a whole — let alone the population as a whole.&#8221;</p>
<p>Keep it up, Mr Parris.</p>
</div>
