        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-221721" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-221721" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Bilge! This article emphasises exactly what is wrong with the party.</p>
</div>
        </div>

    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
    <li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="dsq-comment-221751">
        <div id="dsq-comment-header-221751" class="dsq-comment-header">
            <cite id="dsq-cite-221751">
                <span id="dsq-author-user-221751">Reconstruct</span>
            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-221751" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-221751" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>I have never been allowed a vote on our participation in the EU institution. Since they evidently do have power to make rules which I must obey or be punished for disobeying, this is wrong and, yes, oppressive. </p>
<p>Several times politicians have promised me that I can have a vote on this, only for the promise to be rescinded.  Since this behaviour has been shared by all the major parties, I do think this is a conspiracy. </p>
<p>And, oh yes, before I forget, these unaccountable people have condemned entire generations of Southern Europeans to poverty and despair, primarily in order to support their own cruelly stupid vanity-project. Frankly, yes, I do think that&#8217;s wicked. </p>
<p>So I guess I&#8217;m an extremist. Thanks Matthew, for clearing that up.</p>
</div>
        </div>

    <ul class="children">
    <li class="comment odd alt depth-2" id="dsq-comment-221911">
        <div id="dsq-comment-header-221911" class="dsq-comment-header">
            <cite id="dsq-cite-221911">
                <span id="dsq-author-user-221911">martin_lowe</span>
            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-221911" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-221911" class="dsq-comment-message"><p><i>I have never been allowed a vote on our participation in the EU institution.</i></p>
<p>So you&#8217;ve never voted in a General Election, then?</p>
</div>
        </div>

    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
    <li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="dsq-comment-221841">
        <div id="dsq-comment-header-221841" class="dsq-comment-header">
            <cite id="dsq-cite-221841">
                <span id="dsq-author-user-221841">terence patrick hewett</span>
            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-221841" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-221841" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Two Labour Councillors and four Tory have crossed.  Not a bad day for UKIP.</p>
</div>
        </div>

    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
    <li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="dsq-comment-221891">
        <div id="dsq-comment-header-221891" class="dsq-comment-header">
            <cite id="dsq-cite-221891">
                <span id="dsq-author-user-221891">Bill_der_Berg</span>
            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-221891" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-221891" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>&#8220;Last Saturday I wrote for my newspaper a column whose drift was that it was time for the sane majority of the Conservative party to repel those elements on the Tory right who plainly wish the Prime Minister and the coalition ill&#8230; etc&#8230;etc&#8217;</p>
<p>An excellent way of repelling  people is to call them bigots.  Ask Gordon Brown.   It worked a treat for him.</p>
</div>
        </div>

    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
    <li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="dsq-comment-221941">
        <div id="dsq-comment-header-221941" class="dsq-comment-header">
            <cite id="dsq-cite-221941">
                <span id="dsq-author-user-221941">David Gale</span>
            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-221941" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-221941" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Two words to replace the wordy missive above: &#8216;space&#8217; and &#8216;democracy&#8217;. Not really too much to ask, is it?</p>
</div>
        </div>

    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
    <li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="dsq-comment-222141">
        <div id="dsq-comment-header-222141" class="dsq-comment-header">
            <cite id="dsq-cite-222141">
                <span id="dsq-author-user-222141">terence patrick hewett</span>
            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-222141" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-222141" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Matthew Parris and several of the commenters have described UKIP as rude and extremist and worse.  Well, robust  yes; extremist, hardly.   British politics is confrontational not consensual and with its tradition of satire, scandal and sedition is about settling old scores, real or imagined and we can hardly wait to put the boot in.  There are areas of discussion where the liberal mainstream display all the sensibilities of a Victorian maiden aunt and if they enter into debate on the interweb wishing simply to hear the echo of their own voice they will be sadly disappointed.</p>
<p> Try bringing up the subject of the effects of population displacement and the resultant destabilisation upon country, society and liberty.  Try the classical Christian doctrine that the promotion of pederasty and sapphism are anarchic, sterile, hedonistic, and socially damaging pastimes which destabilise the family and society.  Try postulating that the introduction of euthanasia and abortion, turn us into a nation of old people, further the task of population reduction, damage the fabric of family and society and are intrinsically evil.   Try suggesting that the debauchment of the education system is a deliberate policy to reduce a sense of identity and to produce an ignorant and supine untermensch.  Try  pointing out that the left, using entryism, and with previous points in mind, have corrupted the integrity of the schools, the judiciary, the civil service, local government, councils, the social services, the BBC and the police, and have also made a start on the armed forces.</p>
<p>Try the hypothesis that the left having rejected the set of absolute moral values willed to it by Christianity and Judaism and no longer having a coherent set of moral ethics, have filled the vacuum with a mess of single conflicting issues, which in the words of Phillip Blond, have &#8220;repudiated and vilified the very structure and basis of society itself.&#8221; </p>
<p> Try all that and you will be in for a very dusty time; you will be cast into the outer darkness with rudeness and discourtesy.  Great as the temptation is to snigger at all this pompous maiden auntery, they are the most serious issues of our age and need to be debated since they affect the very nature of self and how we see our future.  In the end reality always breaks in, and the longer we leave it the more traumatic it will be when it does. Leonard Shapiro wrote of Soviet Russia that &#8220;the true object of propaganda is neither to convince nor even to persuade, but to produce a uniform pattern of public utterance in which the first trace of unorthodox thought reveals itself as a jarring dissonance.&#8221;</p>
</div>
        </div>

    <ul class="children">
    <li class="comment even depth-2" id="dsq-comment-229101">
        <div id="dsq-comment-header-229101" class="dsq-comment-header">
            <cite id="dsq-cite-229101">
                <span id="dsq-author-user-229101">Jonathan Kuperberg</span>
            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-229101" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-229101" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Wow! Pro-life, pro-family, anti-secular humanism,&#8230; you got me <img src="http://cdn.spectator.co.uk/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" /> </p>
</div>
        </div>

    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
    <li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="dsq-comment-222601">
        <div id="dsq-comment-header-222601" class="dsq-comment-header">
            <cite id="dsq-cite-222601">
                <span id="dsq-author-user-222601">Robert Taggart</span>
            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-222601" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-222601" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>What is so  wrong with extremism ?<br />
Blighty politics be far to monochrome &#8211; they need some &#8216;colour&#8217; !<br />
Thankyou, Gorgeous George, Nadine &#8216;Jane&#8217; Dories, Nigel Farage&#8230; !</p>
</div>
        </div>

    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
    <li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="dsq-comment-222641">
        <div id="dsq-comment-header-222641" class="dsq-comment-header">
            <cite id="dsq-cite-222641">
                <span id="dsq-author-user-222641">Bob339</span>
            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-222641" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-222641" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>There are (officially) 36,000,000 muslims in Europe. ( God alone knows what the actual number is but I suspect it is considerably higher!).<br />
All these folk are breeding like bunnies. They are beginning to get stroppy, demanding shariah law zones, killing soldiers in the street, planning bomb attacks against the EDL in Dewsbury. Enoch is beginning to look like a prophet.<br />
 We may still avoid the coming crap times if government acts now. Dave, Tony, Millipede, Clegg&#8230;well they are not the boys to say the least.</p>
<p>Mathew Parris &#8211; a nice enough bloke in his way- I suppose, but he lives in a parallel universe and does not give a swing about non-political people whatever their class,<br />
(just like all his pals in parliament). He has lost touch with the world we live in.</p>
<p>So what can he tell us about extremism? About events in Woolwich he is oddly silent.<br />
About the hatemongers all over the internet he has nowt to report.<br />
But about a possible threat to the Tory party he waxes almost lyrical in his bid to do them down.</p>
<p>Matt, baby, learn this, take it to heart: the time is rapidly coming when we need extremism, when we will have to act to save our culture, our society. Wake up, smell the onions.</p>
</div>
        </div>

    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
    <li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="dsq-comment-224031">
        <div id="dsq-comment-header-224031" class="dsq-comment-header">
            <cite id="dsq-cite-224031">
                <span id="dsq-author-user-224031">Joe Smith</span>
            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-224031" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-224031" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Perhaps Mr Parris could explain why opinion polls for the European Elections next year have UKIP way ahead of Dave and his chums. Are all these people extremists? Or do they like a party which trusts the British people to make up their own minds on who governs Britian? You may have decided that the EU is a good thing &#8211; but that does not give you and your friends the right to dictate to everyone else! And as for describing the EU as a tyranny, who ignored the stated wishes of the people of France Holland and Ireland over the Lisbon Treaty? Who, after Denmark and Sweden both rejected the Euro, refused to have a referendum in any one of the 17 Eurozone memebers on whether they join the currency? Who removed the democratically elected cabinets of Italy and Greece and replaced them with unelected EU puppets? How would Mr Parris feel if every member of the British Cabinet had been taken from the House of Lords and The Prime Minister was Peter Mandleson? And I nearly forgot, which is the only body in the EU which can propose or repeal EU legislation?</p>
</div>
        </div>

    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
    <li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="dsq-comment-235621">
        <div id="dsq-comment-header-235621" class="dsq-comment-header">
            <cite id="dsq-cite-235621">
                <span id="dsq-author-user-235621">UKIP Chapel &amp; Hope</span>
            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-235621" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-235621" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>During the last election when I was a UKIP candidate, Mathew Parris had some fun in his column upon discovering that my email address was &#8216;madasafish&#8217;. Let me confirm his opinion. I am mad. Why? Because I think that I was born free (in 1967) and am now not free. That is because I cannot sack through the ballot box those people who make the laws and rules that govern my life when i do not like the laws that they make. Many of those rules come directly or indirectly from the EU. The ability to decide who makes the rules by which we live is surely an essential component of democracy. The really terrible thing is that my right to choose my lawmakers through the ballot box was not taken from me by a foreign power. It was given away by those who through their election to Parliament, were entrusted with the protection of my rights. So, yes Mathew. I am mad. Mad with indignation and mad with anger on behalf not just of myself, but of those who sacrificed so much in numerous conflicts in order to protect my freedoms. I do not think this has come about through some Machiavellian conspiracy of betrayal but betrayal is nevertheless the cumulative effect of a thousand acts of individual cowardice, greed or wrong- thinking ideology. </p>
</div>
        </div>

    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
    <li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="dsq-comment-254051">
        <div id="dsq-comment-header-254051" class="dsq-comment-header">
            <cite id="dsq-cite-254051">
                <span id="dsq-author-user-254051">CanadianDude2000</span>
            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-254051" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-254051" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Canadian here. I came across this article. It&#8217;s infuriating to read. When you call a political party extremist, that is harsh word. It is a word reserved for people who are clearly racist or violent. At the very least, they must materially support such groups. (Not a one-off thing but whose party regularly calls for violence or supports it openly.) There are tons of parties in Europe, either right wing or Islamic, which openly do this. Ukip is not one of them, so far as I see at this time.</p>
<p>I hate to say it, but it&#8217;s very clear to me, and many North Americans that Britain doesn&#8217;t really care about its culture.</p>
</div>
        </div>

    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
    <li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="dsq-comment-258011">
        <div id="dsq-comment-header-258011" class="dsq-comment-header">
            <cite id="dsq-cite-258011">
                <span id="dsq-author-user-258011">Domlingus</span>
            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-258011" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-258011" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Congratulations! Spoken like a true left wing fascist with a complete disregard for truth!</p>
</div>
        </div>

    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
    <li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="dsq-comment-258021">
        <div id="dsq-comment-header-258021" class="dsq-comment-header">
            <cite id="dsq-cite-258021">
                <span id="dsq-author-user-258021">Domlingus</span>
            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-258021" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-258021" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Facts, rather than wishful thinking and carefully selected comments, often out of context, is sure to bolster your argument, fortunately the truth is somewhat different.</p>
<p>The United Kingdom Independence Party leader welcomed news that the local<br />
and European elections will be held on the same day, 22 May 2014.</p>
<p>The change is seen by experts as a boost for Ukip because it will<br />
increase turnout for the Euro elections, which Mr Farage is hoping to<br />
win.</p>
<p>In August, last year, David Cameron was forced to shelve plans to introduce elected peers after failing to win over Conservative rebels. He proposed<br />
instead that the appointment of peers should be based on the results<br />
of the previous General Election.</p>
<p>Under the scheme the United Kingdom Independent Party would have a total of<br />
24 peers, compared to the three that they have at present.</p>
<p>As voters in previous True blue counties affected by the devastation of the EU ordered HS2 have come to realise, far from being an extremist party, Ukip is true Tory, this discovery influenced the Council elections in May showed clearly the UKIP won directly down the HS2 line starting with Great Missenden. (hardly extremist territory)  the Tory vote share fell from 65% 4 years ago to 37% !</p>
<p
8000
>Facts and truth are always so much more preferable and far less extremist than the wishful thinking and and left wing fascist ideology expressed in your article!</p>
</div>
        </div>

    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
    <li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="dsq-comment-258241">
        <div id="dsq-comment-header-258241" class="dsq-comment-header">
            <cite id="dsq-cite-258241">
                <span id="dsq-author-user-258241">gaswork</span>
            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-258241" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-258241" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Our national debt has reached more than £1 trillion<br />
simply shows the unsustainable level of spending this country built up over the<br />
past 30 years, and shows why it is critical for our nation&#8217;s future that we<br />
deal decisively with the deficit as a now new Ukip supporter or Ex labour I find<br />
that News papers views are basted on Hypocrisy pretending<br />
to have virtues, moral or religious beliefs, principles, etc., that one does<br />
not actually have. Hypocrisy involves the deception of others and is thus a<br />
kind of lie welcome to the News papers if you can not see the last 30 years of<br />
political lies in order to gain power then I can understand why you vote lab or<br />
them cons or libs,</p>
</div>
        </div>

    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
    <li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="dsq-comment-361321">
        <div id="dsq-comment-header-361321" class="dsq-comment-header">
            <cite id="dsq-cite-361321">
                <span id="dsq-author-user-361321">andyrwebman</span>
            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-361321" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-361321" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>The contention that there is no single root cause, no single common thread is amusing. It leads you to the conclusion that somehow the left created this perfect storm of cock ups entirely by accident. </p>
<p>The thing is, even if you don&#8217;t think of them as aprt of a conspiracy, you can see how they result from the kind of minds which are stuck on an ideological path which totally ignores empirical evidence, and which frankly should be rejected by any intellect above that of a ten year old.</p>
<p>As for the liberal elite &#8211; tell me, if they don&#8217;t exist then how did mass immigration occur when it has been consistently opposed by the vast majority of the population? </p>
<p>It&#8217;s not just immigration, everywhere I go I hear people feeling generally annoyed by the petty little restrictions on free speech, how careful you have to be not to offend people (the so called &#8220;Equality Act&#8221; which few people like) and a load of other things. </p>
<p>Somewhere in government or the civil service, people are quietly side stepping democracy by making the changes piecemeal, small enough to slip beneath the radar in the main, until one day you wake up and realise your freedoms have gone and you don&#8217;t recognise your own country.</p>
</div>
        </div>

    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
    <li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="dsq-comment-501232">
        <div id="dsq-comment-header-501232" class="dsq-comment-header">
            <cite id="dsq-cite-501232">
                <span id="dsq-author-user-501232">James Allen</span>
            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-501232" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-501232" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Given the success of your political career, it&#8217;s rather ironic you get paid to write about politics! Or is that just me being unkind&#8230;.?</p>
</div>
        </div>

    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
    <li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="dsq-comment-513272">
        <div id="dsq-comment-header-513272" class="dsq-comment-header">
            <cite id="dsq-cite-513272">
http://www.biologymad.com/                <span id="dsq-author-user-513272">HD2</span>
            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-513272" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-513272" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>UKIP&#8217;s growth has been caused by the dire incompetence of the politicians who have infested the UK since 1945.<br />
The same narrow coterie of socialist-minded simpletons, also populate Whitehall and the major organs of The Establishment.</p>
<p>Few are scientists: none biologists, for every act of the above groups has sought to deny the most basic and fundamental of truths: that Darwinism has beaten Marxism throughout the last 4.5 billion years.</p>
<p>Darwinism requires diversity, selection/competition and time to allow for change/evolution.</p>
<p>Marxism requires a single, centrally-imposed solution to every problem: the antithesis to Darwinism.</p>
<p>So, every time the Media conjure up a &#8216;problem case&#8217;, the CORRECT answer is &#8216;Then we must abolish the rules and regulations which created this insanity and allow common-sense and LOCAL decision-making to prevail&#8217;.</p>
<p>Unless and until we regain that mind-set, we&#8217;re doomed to sclerosis and economic and social death.</p>
</div>
        </div>

    </li><!-- #comment-## -->
    <li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="dsq-comment-565031">
        <div id="dsq-comment-header-565031" class="dsq-comment-header">
